00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:19,440
of a couple of magnets nearby

274
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,440
and wiggle them a little bit.

275
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,440
And the effect of that wiggling a little bit

276
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:26,440
will be to create spin waves, or magnons,

277
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:29,440
and those magnons can propagate from one, uh,

278
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:31,440
from one person to another,

279
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:33,440
can send messages with them,

280
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:36,440
and those people living in this ferromagnet

281
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:39,440
after they've done lots of experiments

282
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:41,440
with these spin waves

283
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,440
will conclude from experiment

284
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:46,440
that those spin waves are massless,

285
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,440
that it costs no energy to

286
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,440
make very, very long wavelength ones.

287
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,440
If they were smart, they would conclude

288
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,440
that they're living in a

289
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:56,440
world of spontaneous symmetry breaking

290
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:58,940
and not that the fundamental

291
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:01,440
properties of the world are asymmetric.

292
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:04,440
It's just that the world that they live in,

293
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,440
the energies are such

294
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,440
that it tends to align everything,

295
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:11,440
but it doesn't matter which direction things align in.

296
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:13,440
That's the basic phenomenon

297
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,440
of spontaneous symmetry breaking.

298
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:18,940
It does not have to, necessarily have

299
00:15:18,940 --> 00:15:22,440
to do with, uh, rotations of real space.

300
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:24,940
It could have to do with

301
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:27,440
all of, or all of, or any

302
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:31,440
of the internal symmetry groups of particle physics.

303
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:34,440
In particular, things like SU3-quadrant,

304
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:37,440
things like SU3-cross SU2-cross U1, and so forth.

305
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:42,440
One of the things that we learned, incidentally,

306
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:47,440
is that there's a kind of interaction

307
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:52,440
between gauge forces and goldstone bosons,

308
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:54,440
which has an effect which I'll come to,

309
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,440
which I'll remind you of later.

310
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:59,440
Anybody remember what the effect of mixing up together,

311
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:03,440
uh, spontaneous symmetry breaking and gauge invariance was?

312
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:07,940
Goldstone, uh, boson went away and became

313
00:16:07,940 --> 00:16:11,440
an extra, uh, uh, parameter for the, uh,

314
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,440
For the gauge boson.

315
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:14,440
Became, that's right.

316
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,440
It, uh, turned the gauge boson

317
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:18,440
to a massive thing instead of massless.

318
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,440
And we'll come back to this.

319
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,940
We'll come back to this theme, but

320
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,440
I just want to remind you of it.

321
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,440
That was the pattern, or

322
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,440
the idea, of spontaneous symmetry breaking,

323
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:30,440
continuous spontaneous symmetry breaking.

324
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:33,440
There's also another mathematical statement,

325
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:36,440
one can make.

326
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:41,440
The vacuum, of course, being the state of lowest energy,

327
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:45,440
is just any one of these configurations

328
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,440
where the magnets, in this, in this particular context,

329
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,440
of course, of a ferromagnet,

330
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,440
where all the, uh, ferromagnets

331
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,440
are aligned along the same direction.

332
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,440
There's a, there's a vacuum for that direction,

333
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,440
there's a vacuum for that direction,

334
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:00,440
there's a vacuum for that direction.

335
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:02,440
Nobody in the world is big enough to get outside

336
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:05,440
and make, uh, rotate from one to the other,

337
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:08,440
so all of physics takes place in one of them,

338
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:11,440
and the people living in that vacuum in that world

339
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,440
call that configuration the vacuum.

340
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:17,440
Okay, so there are many vacuums.

341
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:22,440
Uh, let's take the vacuum that they live in,

342
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:26,440
and let's apply to it the symmetry operation.

343
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:29,440
The symmetry operation means the generators of the symmetry.

344
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,440
What are the generators of rotation symmetry?

345
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:35,440
The components of the angular momentum.

346
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:38,440
Angular momentum, sometimes I call it J,

347
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,940
sometimes I call it L,

348
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:41,440
let's call it J right now,

349
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:44,440
since it consists of all the angular momentum of everything.

350
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,440
Let's call it J.

351
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,440
And what does J do

352
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:50,440
when it acts on a state?

353
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:54,440
It infinitesimally rotates it a little bit, right?

354
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:57,440
It infinitesimally rotates it a little bit.

355
00:17:57,440 --> 00:18:00,440
If...

356
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:07,440
the vacuum state was such that it really was symmetric,

357
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:09,440
that it really didn't have

358
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,440
this kind of spontaneous symmetry breaking,

359
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:17,440
what would happen... what would happen, uh, if you, uh...

360
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:21,440
if you rotated the state a little bit?

361
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,440
It would come back to itself, right?

362
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,940
Now, you have to remember that this

363
00:18:24,940 --> 00:18:26,440
is, uh, this is the difference between...

364
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,440
J really represents the difference

365
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:30,440
between the rotation and the nonrotation.

366
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:33,440
It's not the rotated state.

367
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:37,440
It's the little infinitesimal change in the state

368
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:42,440
that's made by, uh, by a small rotation.

369
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:46,440
J corresponds to a small change in the state.

370
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:51,440
If the state, the vacuum state, was symmetric,

371
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:55,440
then when you apply J to it, nothing happens.

372
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,440
And the right-hand side is just zero.

373
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,440
No change whatever in the state.

374
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,440
Uh...

375
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,440
From a formal mathematical point of view,

376
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:08,440
the signal of spontaneous symmetry breaking

377
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,440
is that J, when it acts

378
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:12,440
on the vacuum, doesn't give zero.

379
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,440
It gives a state which is slightly rotated.

380
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:17,440
So, not equal to zero

381
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:23,440
means that the vacuum has a spontaneous symmetry breaking.

382
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:26,440
Now, we're gonna see that pattern repeat itself

383
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:28,440
in supersymmetry

384
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,440
with the exception of the

385
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:31,440
with the exception, of course,

386
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:33,440
that the symmetry, or the generators,

387
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,440
are these fermionic objects.

388
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,440
Oh, incidentally, what...

389
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:39,440
Let's, uh, let's suppose that

390
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,440
J on the vacuum,

391
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:43,440
rotate the vacuum, does not give zero.

392
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:45,440
Then what does it give?

393
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,440
What does it give?

394
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,440
Well...

395
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:51,440
It has the same vacuum.

396
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,440
It doesn't give the same vacuum.

397
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:55,440
It gives a slightly rotated one.

398
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,440
But the slightly rotated one

399
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:00,440
is equivalent to putting into the system

400
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:04,440
an infinitely long wavelength goldstone boson.

401
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,440
So you could say that

402
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:11,440
J on the vacuum creates a very, very long wavelength,

403
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:14,440
infinitely long wavelength goldstone boson.

404
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:17,440
Does J on the vacuum change the energy?

405
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,440
No.

406
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:21,440
It just rotated the vacuum a little bit.

407
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:25,440
And so, J, when it acts on the vacuum,

408
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:28,440
it gives a goldstone boson state.

409
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:30,440
Let's call it a Gb.

410
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,440
It gives a goldstone boson state.

411
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,440
And the fact that rotating the vacuum

412
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:37,440
doesn't cost any energy at all

413
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,440
tells us that the goldstone boson

414
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:41,440
has no energy.

415
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:43,440
This is the pattern.

416
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:45,440
Uh...

417
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,440
One more point.

418
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:53,440
All these points are important.

419
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:54,440
The magnetic field,

420
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:57,440
the magnetization of the ferromagnet,

421
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:59,440
is described by a little vector,

422
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:01,440
by a vector.

423
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,440
It's a vector at each point of space,

424
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:05,440
and so it can be thought of as a field.

425
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:09,440
It's the local properties of the ferromagnet.

426
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,440
And that little vector, of course,

427
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:13,440
is nothing but the direction

428
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,440
of the little magnetic moments

429
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:17,440
that are making up the direction and magnitude

430
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:18,440
of the magnetic moments

431
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:20,440
that are making up the ferromagnet.

432
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,440
And you can call it M.

433
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,440
It's not the same M.

434
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,440
It's capital M.

435
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,440
Capital M.

436
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,440
And it's a vector.

437
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:29,440
It points along the axis of the ferromagnets.

438
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:31,440
Um...

439
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,440
If M is zero,

440
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,440
that could be the case,

441
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,440
for example,

442
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:45,440
in a warm ferromagnet.

443
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,440
If you heat a ferromagnet up,

444
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,440
then the magnets fluctuate

445
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:51,440
and on the average,

446
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:53,440
there's no net magnetization.

447
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:55,440
In quantum mechanics,

448
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:57,440
it just may be that quantum fluctuations

449
00:21:57,440 --> 00:22:00,440
wash out the magnetization.

450
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,440
If M equals zero,

451
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:03,440
that's the situation

452
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:05,440
where we say the vacuum is symmetric.

453
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,440
There is no magnetization.

454
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,440
If any component of M

455
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:12,440
is not equal to zero,

456
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:14,440
that's another way to represent

457
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:17,440
spontaneous symmetry breaking.

458
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,440
If any component of M

459
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,440
is not equal to zero,

460
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:22,440
then the system is magnetized,

461
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:24,440
along that direction.

462
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:27,440
And if you rotate that component,

463
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:31,440
other components will become non-zero.

464
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:33,440
All right?

465
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,440
So if the Z component is non-zero,

466
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:37,440
and you rotate the ferromagnet,

467
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:41,440
the X component may become non-zero,

468
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,440
or the Y component may become non-zero.

469
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:45,440
So all of these things

470
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:49,440
are the mathematical and physical correlates

471
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:51,440
of the idea of spontaneous symmetry breaking.

472
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:54,440
Okay, now let's review

473
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:57,440
a little bit about supersymmetry,

474
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,440
and I'm going to add a little bit to it.

475
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,440
We're not...

476
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,440
I haven't finished torturing you yet,

477
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,440
tormenting you.

478
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:06,440
We're going to add just a little bit.

479
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,440
If we want to do

480
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:08,440
it, we got to do it.

481
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:10,440
Let's just review.

482
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:13,440
We worked out a single example

483
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:16,440
of a supersymmetric quantum field theory,

484
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,440
or a supersymmetric field theory.

485
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,440
It involved one field,

486
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:23,440
it involved one fermion and one boson field,

487
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:25,440
and I'll just remind you about it.

488
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:27,440
Uh...

489
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:33,440
It involved a superfield

