00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:36,440
that I called capital Phi.

491
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,440
And capital Phi had the property

492
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:41,440
of being a chiral superfield.

493
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:44,440
I won't bother you with the definition of that now,

494
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:47,440
but the important thing about the chiral superfield

495
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:50,440
is that in one form or another,

496
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:53,440
it really only depends on two variables,

497
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:56,440
y and theta.

498
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:58,440
And I'll just remind you,

499
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:00,440
just to put up the equations here,

500
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:03,440
y was equal to the ordinary coordinate x

501
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:06,440
plus i theta bar sigma theta.

502
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:09,440
And that was called a chiral superfield.

503
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,440
Okay?

504
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:12,440
It's also complex.

505
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:14,440
It's important that it's complex,

506
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:16,440
and if you wanted to try to make it real,

507
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:18,440
what you would find

508
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:21,440
is that a supersymmetric transformation

509
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:23,440
would generate an imaginary part.

510
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:25,440
So it's not consistent with supersymmetry

511
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:27,440
to say that it's real.

512
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,440
That was Phi,

