00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:47,820
Do you know what an atom looks like

1213
00:56:47,820 --> 00:56:50,820
when it's in an incredibly strong magnetic field?

1214
00:56:52,820 --> 00:56:56,820
A long stringy spaghetti-ish looking thing.

1215
00:56:56,820 --> 00:56:57,820
Right.

1216
00:56:57,820 --> 00:56:59,820
The atom would be unrecognizable.

1217
00:56:59,820 --> 00:57:01,820
But if the magnetic field is very weak,

1218
00:57:01,820 --> 00:57:04,820
then the atom is quite recognizable.

1219
00:57:04,820 --> 00:57:06,820
And what you would say,

1220
00:57:06,820 --> 00:57:09,820
and that's the situation we're going to be interested in,

1221
00:57:09,820 --> 00:57:12,820
the situation where the magnetic field

1222
00:57:12,820 --> 00:57:14,820
due to the ferromagnet...

1223
00:57:14,820 --> 00:57:17,820
We're not interested in ferromagnets, but by analogy,

1224
00:57:17,820 --> 00:57:21,820
the magnetic field of the ferromagnet is very weak.

1225
00:57:21,820 --> 00:57:25,820
The atoms are ordinary atoms,

1226
00:57:25,820 --> 00:57:30,820
and their levels are only slightly split.

1227
00:57:30,820 --> 00:57:33,820
The reason we're interested in that situation

1228
00:57:33,820 --> 00:57:36,820
is because compared to the fundamental

1229
00:57:36,820 --> 00:57:40,820
scale of particle physics, string theory,

1230
00:57:40,820 --> 00:57:42,820
grand unified theories, or anything like that,

1231
00:57:42,820 --> 00:57:46,820
which tends to be up at 16 orders of magnitude

1232
00:57:46,820 --> 00:57:48,820
larger than the particle physics scale,

1233
00:57:48,820 --> 00:57:50,820
the splitting of the superpartners

1234
00:57:50,820 --> 00:57:52,820
is hoped to be very small.

1235
00:57:52,820 --> 00:57:54,820
It's hoped that the superpartners

1236
00:57:54,820 --> 00:57:57,820
have almost the same mass on that scale

1237
00:57:57,820 --> 00:57:59,820
as ordinary particles.

1238
00:57:59,820 --> 00:58:02,820
That would be analogous to the magnetic field

1239
00:58:02,820 --> 00:58:05,820
due to the ferromagnet being very weak,

1240
00:58:05,820 --> 00:58:09,820
and only splitting these particles a little bit.

1241
00:58:09,820 --> 00:58:12,820
If the magnetic field were very weak,

1242
00:58:12,820 --> 00:58:15,820
the atoms would hardly notice it.

1243
00:58:15,820 --> 00:58:17,820
They would hardly notice it,

1244
00:58:17,820 --> 00:58:20,820
they would hardly interact with those magnetic fields,

1245
00:58:20,820 --> 00:58:23,820
and in fact, one of the consequences of this

1246
00:58:23,820 --> 00:58:26,820
would be that it's rather hard

1247
00:58:26,820 --> 00:58:29,820
by manipulating the atom...

1248
00:58:29,820 --> 00:58:32,820
by manipulating the atom

1249
00:58:32,820 --> 00:58:34,820
to influence the ferromagnet

1250
00:58:34,820 --> 00:58:35,820
because the ferromagnet,

1251
00:58:35,820 --> 00:58:37,820
they're too weakly coupled,

1252
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:39,820
and so manipulating the atom

1253
00:58:39,820 --> 00:58:42,820
would not be likely to stir up spin waves,

1254
00:58:42,820 --> 00:58:45,820
would not be likely to stir up these...

1255
00:58:45,820 --> 00:58:48,820
the properties of the ferromagnet itself.

1256
00:58:50,820 --> 00:58:53,820
And in the language that we use,

1257
00:58:53,820 --> 00:58:55,820
the ferromagnet would correspond

1258
00:58:55,820 --> 00:58:57,820
to what's called a hidden sector.

1259
00:58:57,820 --> 00:59:00,820
It's a hidden sector in that

1260
00:59:00,820 --> 00:59:03,820
unless this was a very sophisticated atom,

1261
00:59:03,820 --> 00:59:09,820
it wouldn't even notice the ferromagnet.

1262
00:59:09,820 --> 00:59:11,820
It would just be tiny, tiny splittings,

1263
00:59:11,820 --> 00:59:16,820
and the ferromagnet would be a hidden sector.

1264
00:59:16,820 --> 00:59:17,820
In the same way,

1265
00:59:17,820 --> 00:59:20,820
particle physics, supersymmetric quantum mechanics

1266
00:59:20,820 --> 00:59:23,820
also requires hidden sectors

1267
00:59:23,820 --> 00:59:27,820
and additions of new objects and new particles

1268
00:59:27,820 --> 00:59:30,820
in order to break the supersymmetry.

1269
00:59:30,820 --> 00:59:32,820
It's not a pretty business.

1270
00:59:33,820 --> 00:59:36,820
It's a contrived business.

1271
00:59:36,820 --> 00:59:37,820
You have to add particles,

1272
00:59:37,820 --> 00:59:38,820
you have to add fields.

1273
00:59:38,820 --> 00:59:39,820
By the time you're finished,

1274
00:59:39,820 --> 00:59:42,820
you have a rather complicated construction,

1275
00:59:42,820 --> 00:59:46,820
and a complicated construction is necessary

1276
00:59:46,820 --> 00:59:49,820
to split among the fermions and the bosons.

1277
00:59:49,820 --> 00:59:51,820
That's...

1278
00:59:51,820 --> 00:59:54,820
and the ingredient which does it

1279
00:59:54,820 --> 00:59:56,820
is often called a hidden sector.

1280
00:59:56,820 --> 00:59:58,820
It's the thing which precipitates

1281
00:59:58,820 --> 01:00:00,820
the symmetry breaking.

1282
01:00:00,820 --> 01:00:02,820
Those are some...

1283
