1448
01:06:21,820 --> 01:06:25,820
It has spin 1, but only 2 states.

1449
01:06:25,820 --> 01:06:26,820
Okay?

1450
01:06:26,820 --> 01:06:28,820
If the...

1451
01:06:28,820 --> 01:06:29,820
Um...

1452
01:06:29,820 --> 01:06:31,820
Let's see...

1453
01:06:31,820 --> 01:06:34,820
I don't know why I want to say this.

1454
01:06:34,820 --> 01:06:35,820
Yeah.

1455
01:06:35,820 --> 01:06:37,820
Then you would tell me

1456
01:06:37,820 --> 01:06:39,820
there's something inconsistent about this.

1457
01:06:39,820 --> 01:06:42,820
You would say, if the photon has a mass,

1458
01:06:42,820 --> 01:06:44,820
you can Lorentz transform it,

1459
01:06:44,820 --> 01:06:47,820
or equivalently run along and keep up with the photon

1460
01:06:47,820 --> 01:06:49,820
so that it has no momentum,

1461
01:06:49,820 --> 01:06:51,820
but a spin.

1462
01:06:51,820 --> 01:06:53,320
Lorentz transforming it doesn't change

1463
01:06:53,320 --> 01:06:54,820
the fact that it's a spin.

1464
01:06:54,820 --> 01:06:57,820
So, let's take this spin state here,

1465
01:06:57,820 --> 01:06:59,820
and Lorentz transform it

1466
01:06:59,820 --> 01:07:02,820
so that we're moving up along with it.

1467
01:07:02,820 --> 01:07:05,820
The photon no longer has any momentum,

1468
01:07:05,820 --> 01:07:07,820
