1508
01:08:38,819 --> 01:08:42,819
where the spin along the direction of motion was zero.

1509
01:08:42,819 --> 01:08:46,819
Plus one, minus one,

1510
01:08:46,819 --> 01:08:50,819
and no spin along the z-axis at all altogether.

1511
01:08:50,819 --> 01:08:51,819
Where does that extra component

1512
01:08:51,819 --> 01:08:53,819
of the spin come from

1513
01:08:53,819 --> 01:08:55,819
so that the photon,

1514
01:08:55,819 --> 01:08:57,819
or not the photon,

1515
01:08:57,819 --> 01:08:59,819
but let's say the z-boson

1516
01:08:59,819 --> 01:09:01,819
or the w-boson can be massive?

1517
01:09:01,819 --> 01:09:02,819
Where does it come from?

1518
01:09:02,819 --> 01:09:05,819
And it comes from the goldstone boson.

1519
01:09:05,819 --> 01:09:07,819
The goldstone boson,

1520
01:09:07,819 --> 01:09:13,819
together with the two polarization states,

1521
01:09:13,819 --> 01:09:16,819
the two spin states of the massless z and w,

1522
01:09:16,819 --> 01:09:18,819
combine together

1523
01:09:18,819 --> 01:09:20,819
and make enough states to be the massive,

1524
01:09:20,819 --> 01:09:22,819
the massive z and w,

1525
01:09:22,819 --> 01:09:25,819
which requires three states.

1526
01:09:25,819 --> 01:09:29,819
The same exact thing happens

1527
01:09:29,819 --> 01:09:32,819
when you combine two particles

1528
01:09:32,819 --> 01:09:34,819
from a supersymmetric theory.

1529
01:09:34,819 --> 01:09:36,819
The two particles are, first of all,

1530
01:09:36,819 --> 01:09:39,819
the massless gravitino,

1531
01:09:39,819 --> 01:09:40,819
sorry, the massless,

1532
01:09:40,819 --> 01:09:41,819
yeah, the massless,

1533
01:09:41,819 --> 01:09:43,819
sorry, I didn't have,

